<text>Potential Energy Curves and Activation Energy: The Potential of Collisions

Watch the model below and let it run in slow motion. Don&apos;t touch the &quot;model speed&quot; slider, because you will need the model to run slowly to see what happens to the potential energy during a collision. You should see that sometimes the potential energy is increased when things collide and sometimes decreased, but more often the potential spikes up when the atom and molecule collide. 

If you wait long enough you should see a reaction happen. Try to notice what happens to the kinetic and potential energy when this reaction happens. Then, hit the next arrow. 

 
           

